    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-03-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-03-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="487"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d487">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.9531/3–1146</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Draft Message From the <gloss type="from">Joint Chiefs of
                            Staff</gloss> to General of the Army <persName type="to">Douglas
                            MacArthur</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="65" xml:id="d487fn1">Copy transmitted by the Acting State Department
                        member of <gloss target="#t_SWNCC1">SWNCC</gloss> (H. Freeman Matthews) to
                        the State–War–Navy Coordinating Committee on March 11 as a proposed message
                        to be sent to <gloss target="#t_SCAP1">SCAP</gloss>. The Joint Chiefs of
                        Staff sent the message as telegram War 83080, April 4.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                        calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1946-03-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                        notBefore="1946-03-08T00:00:00-05:00">undated</date>
                </dateline>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <p>Reference CA 56512, 30 December.<note n="66" xml:id="d487fn2">Not printed.</note>
                    Subject is travel of Korean business men. <pb facs="0660" n="648"
                        xml:id="pg_648"/>
                    <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Travel is authorized as recommended in reference cable of limited
                            number Korean businessmen to travel at own expense to U.S. for purpose
                            establishing business contacts provided that: <list>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">a</hi>.</label>
                                <item>It is understood this authorization does not involve
                                    commitment to Korean business men to open up trade between U.S.
                                    and Korea or permit U.S. investment Korean industry at any
                                    particular date.</item>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">b</hi>.</label>
                                <item>The Koreans selected are such as would be authorized to
                                    operate under the contemplated licensing system to be
                                    established when trade between Korea and U.S. is opened, in that
                                    these individuals are not engaged in any activities contrary to
                                    purpose of occupation.</item>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">c</hi>.</label>
                                <item>There are available to Korean businessmen sufficient dollars
                                    to pay for their transportation and maintenance while in
                                    U.S.</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Visas can be obtained any U.S. Consulate if Korean group stops on the
                            way at a point where consulate exists. If not, request for waiver visas
                            should be addressed State Department giving names of Koreans and
                            proposed port entry.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Mode of travel should be as determined by you.</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>Above cable suggested by State Department.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
            </div>
